							Everyone knows iPhone photos are marginal, but who
							wants to drag a camera around? When the venue
							provides photography service, your guests get the
							best of both worlds — wallhanger photos without the
							hassle. Groups also LOVE when someone else initiates
							the photo, as it relieves them of the burden of
							pestering a stranger.
						</p>

						<p style={{ marginBottom: `20px` }}>
							The problem has always been distribution of the
							photos — Candid9 solves this with QR code tickets:
							all you do is take their photo, take a photo of a
							ticket, and hand them the ticket. No collecting
							emails or phone numbers.
						</p>
						<p style={{ marginBottom: `20px` }}>
							After taking photos of 1 or more groups, you will
							later edit the photos and easily upload to Candid9.
							It takes about 2 minutes per photo once you get in a
							groove, minimizing your labor cost.
						</p>
						<p style={{ marginBottom: `20px` }}>
							Being such a simple utility, Candid9 is affordable
							with plans starting at $10/month for 100 photos. Try
							it for free today with no credit card, the first 20
							photos are on the house! You'll need 10 minutes, a
							computer, a camera, paper, scissors, and a venue.
						</p>
					</p>
				</div>

				<img
					alt="Photo1"
					width="480"
					height="620"
					src="/assets/photo1.jpg"
				/>
			</header>
		</div>

